article.headline: Tournament MVP Campbell leads Rutgers with 17 points
article.linkText: Almost Paradise: Rutgers wins Jam title game
article.story:
CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Michelle Campbell scored 17 points to lead Rutgers (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) to a 75-60 win over Kentucky in the Paradise Jam title game on Saturday.

Campbell, who had 12 rebounds and shot 5-for-9, was the tournament most valuable player.

Rutgers started the game with a 10-0 run and finished the first half ahead 41-21.

Samantha Mahoney led Kentucky with 15 points.
